data.description: Incredible artist-owned home that has been thoroughly renovated with full attention to detail. Meticulous care and high-quality workmanship is overwhelmingly evident in the reviving of this 1981 home. All new porcelain tile floors, baseboards, trim, and paint are just the introduction. All interior arches have been raised and the living room is now open with a load bearing cedar header above. Two sets of French doors were installed giving access to the rear patio and bright natural light. All new double pane vinyl windows. Kitchen has new custom soft close cabinets and drawers, quartz counters, tile backsplash, single basin sink, new fixtures to match the stainless steel appliances, and a live edge walnut bar. All bedrooms and bathrooms have custom shelving in the closet to maximize storage. The main bedroom now has a new ensuite bathroom. Both bathrooms have new deep soaking tubs, vanities, bluetooth speakers, and fixtures. The secondary bathroom is finished with black river stone and walnut shelves with blue stone inlays while the main bathroom shines with new tile surround. Everything you can think of has been replaced - light fixtures, door hardware, plumbing fixtures, switches, outlets, toilets, water heater, appliances. Entire exterior has been painted and roof is only 5 years old. It's all been done! Even the refrigerator, washer, and dryer can convey. The home has a huge rear yard and is located in a quiet, friendly neighborhood just minutes from Wolf Ranch, Williams Drive, I-35, 195, and 130. This is a one of a kind home that has been masterfully restored and looks even better in person!
